<li><a href="http://www.photonics.com/content/spectra/2003/January/applications/65734.aspx" class="external text" title="http://www.photonics.com/content/spectra/2003/January/applications/65734.aspx" rel="nofollow">Cameras Monitor Rocket Launch</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.crimereduction.gov.uk/cctvminisite4.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.crimereduction.gov.uk/cctvminisite4.htm" rel="nofollow">UK Government pro-CCTV campaign</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.homeoffice.gov.uk/rds/pdfs05/hors292.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.homeoffice.gov.uk/rds/pdfs05/hors292.pdf" rel="nofollow">Assessing the Impact of CCTV, a UK Home office study on the effectiveness of closed-circuit television</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.theregister.co.uk/2001/09/27/face_recognition_useless_for_crowd/" class="external text" title="http://www.theregister.co.uk/2001/09/27/face_recognition_useless_for_crowd/" rel="nofollow">The Register story: Face recognition useless for crowd surveillance</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.ico.gov.uk/Home/for_organisations/topic_specific_guides/cctv.aspx" class="external text" title="http://www.ico.gov.uk/Home/for_organisations/topic_specific_guides/cctv.aspx" rel="nofollow">CCTV Guidance notes</a> from the UK <a href="/wiki/Information_Commissioner%27s_Office" title="Information Commissioner's Office">Information Commissioner's Office</a></li>
